[[202001131731 Hershinow 2014]] draws attention to the idea that Sophia is one of the [[202001160012 inconsistent characters in Tom Jones]]. Many have read her as a superficial allegorical figure of wisdom, whom Tom acquired through his reformation. Her decision to accept him is sometimes seen as inconsistent with that virtuous character. Hershinow argues that her unwise decision is what makes her a rich rather than superficial character.

