"Of course, we know that Tom is not the only one who has seemed to be what he is not; **the novel’s intricate comedic plot depends on dozens of cases of misrecognition and misidentification,*** including a landlord’s belief that Sophia is Jenny Cameron, fugitive mistress of Bonny Prince Charlie. Persons in Fielding’s novel, it would seem, have such imprecise and versatile shapes that they can be literally interchangeable." ([[202001131731 Hershinow 2014]] 376)</Text>
